The paper deals with visual knowledge bases and their applications in computer vision, specifically in scene graph prediction. This falls under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a semi-supervised method that assigns probabilistic relationship labels, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method uses heuristics and a generative model, which are common techniques in machine learning and probabilistic graphical models (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of textual knowledge base completion methods, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with visual question answering and captioning, which are applications of multimedia (cs.MM).
